      • setBaseType

        default <T> CommandParameterBuilder setBaseType(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                                                ArgumentTypeMapper<T> mapper)
        Sets the ArgumentTypeMapper to be used in mapping the CommandParameter. If an ArgumentTypeMapper is registered in ArgumentTypes, it will not be used. The provided ArgumentTypeMapper will not be registered with ArgumentTypes. It is generally recommended to prefer using different flags on custom types to indicate that the CommandArgument should be mapped differently.
        Parameters:
        mapper - a public class that implements ArgumentTypeMapper and contains a no-args public constructor.
